gomodel:SYNGO_2304  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig.6A,B shows that manipulating the expression level of Farp1 in postsynaptic neurons acts across synapses to regulate the intensity of the active zone marker bassoon at the presynaptic inputs these postsynaptic neurons receive. Fig.6C shows that this retrograde trans-synaptic effect of Farp1 depends on SynCAM 1. These results support that postsynaptic Farp1 can modulate the composition of presynaptic active zones.. Experimental description: 1/11/2017 Pim\n- Cells: \"Primary hippocampal neurons were dissected at P0 from rats or SynCAM 1 KO mice\" Cells in Fig.6 are rat (panel A/B) and mouse (panel C/D).\n- The overexpressed Farp1 protein is of rat species: \"To generate a plasmid for the expression of Farp1, the full-length coding sequence was amplified from a rat brain P11 cDNA library\"\n- Mouse annotation can also be made." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0912-1514" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-3670-7863" ;
        dc:date           "2017-12-21" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_2304" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

